I have to update my review, took my three 10lbs dogs in at 1100, they were not ready until 3:30, reason given was "we're busy, it's the holidays" ok, advice, you know how many dogs your staff can complete during a day, utilize that metric when making appointments. If you are "busy" schedule appointments for another day, it's literally that easy. Only schedule the amount of appointments your staff can complete given the hours in a work day, obviously using historical data about cancellations to pad that data. But seriously, four and a half hours to complete two under ten pound dogs haircuts and a wash of a third dog as a wash only is ridiculous and the haircuts were not close to the quality I'm accustomed to at this facility.

Update, spoke to the owner and they are making it right, apologized for the bad haircut and are making it right. Giving me a free groom of both my dogs. Very professional response to my poor experience and I will update again once I return my dogs for a groom. I highly anticipate it to be good since it always was in the past. Currently updated to four stars and if all goes as expected I will definitely upgrade to five.
